body:
@acoven Good point - responsive page management is critical for smooth scrolling. With 50ms debounce, you'd get choppy scroll direction detection and delayed canvas swapping.

Here's what I recommend:

**Option 1: Use requestAnimationFrame (Best)**
```javascript
let scrollScheduled = false;
containerElement.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
  if (!scrollScheduled) {
    scrollScheduled = true;
    requestAnimationFrame(() => {
      try {
        handleScroll();
      } catch (error) {
        console.error('Scroll handler error:', error);
        console.error('Error stack:', error.stack);
      }
      scrollScheduled = false;
    });
  }
});
```

**Option 2: Micro-debounce (10ms)**
```javascript
let scrollTimer = 0;
containerElement.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
  clearTimeout(scrollTimer);
  scrollTimer = window.setTimeout(() => {
    try {
      handleScroll();
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Scroll handler error:', error);
      console.error('Error stack:', error.stack);
    }
  }, 10); // Much smaller delay
});
```

RequestAnimationFrame is ideal because it:
- Syncs with 60fps refresh rate (~16ms intervals)
- Prevents redundant work within the same frame
